The Ebola and Zika virus outbreaks prompted the Obama administration to seek budget supplementals that could have replenished the SNS by 2016, but securing congressional authorization proved challenging.
In 2016, when Congress green-lit funds to combat the Zika virus, the CDC received less than half of what the Obama administration sought.